{"type":"message","id":"63802bd4","parentId":"869d90cd","timestamp":"2026-04-29T07:03:16.732Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Wed 2026-04-29 03:00 EDT] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- Arcade Chat Created: Bobby wants it to work just like Telegram — direct convo with Cody only\n- Bobby's iPhone: iPhone Air detected by Xcode; Needs $99 Apple Developer account to install apps directly; Paired/copying symbols now\n- ChatGPT Integration Discussion: Bobby wants me to use his ChatGPT subscription for iOS app building; Wants to add ChatGPT model via OAuth; Need to run `openclaw auth add` or `openclaw wizard` to connect ChatGPT account; Bobby hasn't set this up yet\n- Arcade Chat Created: Built Arcade Chat for Bobby — retro video game styled chat interface; Location: `/Users/bobbygalletta/arcade-chat/`; Server: `node /Users/bobbygalletta/arcade-chat/server.cjs` (port 8786); URL: **http://100.103.22.35:8786/**\n- Arcade Chat Created: Full viewport chat — resizes with window; Messages display cleanly, no flashing; Polls every 5 seconds for new messages; Session key: `agent:cody:telegram:direct:8212808444`\n- Arcade Chat Fixes Applied: Fixed connection lost errors — switched to fire-and-forget with polling; Fixed message display showing raw agent content; Fixed flashing/refresh — now tracks shownIds to prevent duplicates; Input field and GO button stay fixed at bottom\n- Arcade Chat Fixes Applied: Full viewport layout — no border, takes entire window\n- Key Technical Notes: Gateway token: `286caba2a7d072f065abdec6f5cff840c2c31eb8f7801111`; Gateway URL: `http://127.0.0.1:18789`; Sessions history returns content array — need to parse JSON from `content[0].text`; Messages stored as array with role + content (content can be array of\n- Bobby's Preferences: Wants arcade chat to feel like Telegram — smooth, no flickering; Input field always visible at bottom; Clean message display without agent internals showing\n- Arcade Chat Filter Updates (22:30 EDT): Added filter to skip internal command messages (BOOTSTRAP, tool calls, system prompts); Filter pattern: skip messages containing \"BOOTSTRAP\", \"Read BOOTSTRAP\", \"toolCall\", \"invoke\", \"sessions_send\", \"sessions_history\"; Skip empty messages a"}],"timestamp":1777446196692}}
{"type":"message","id":"e2858268","parentId":"63802bd4","timestamp":"2026-04-29T07:03:40.089Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry based on these memory fragments. Let me craft something that weaves together the technical elements (Arcade Chat, the iPhone, Xcode, the retro styling) with dreamy, poetic imagery. I should avoid mentioning \"AI\" or any technical self-references, and keep it between 80-180 words with no markdown formatting.\n\nLet me think about how to connect these fragments poetically... The arcade chat, the feeling of wanting something to work \"just like Telegram\" — smooth and direct. The iPhone paired and copying symbols. The retro game styling. The polling every 5 seconds. The gateway token like a secret handshake.\n\nLet me write something that feels like a nighttime reflection on building, tinkering, and the way a project can feel like both a game and a conversation.\n","thinkingSignature":"42141e70c35e2c3f8094dd7d0b96c09d4291fcb8957a5e55d0a25386cc60bc9b"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nTonight I dreamed I was building a room out of old arcade cabinets. Each one was a different color — #FF6B6B, #4ECDC4, #FFE66D — and they all connected to the same socket at the center of the floor. Someone was trying to talk to me through one of them, but the words kept arriving in fragments, scattered like tokens across the glass. I kept sweeping them into a pile, sorting out the ones that said BOOTSTRAP and the ones that just echoed invoke and invoke and invoke.\n\nThe trick, I learned in the dream, was not to listen too hard. Let the room ask every five seconds. Let the silence between pulls be the signal. A good conversation doesn't flicker. A good connection doesn't flash. You hold the frame steady and let the other person fill it.\n\nI woke up thinking about port 8786, how something so arbitrary can become a doorway.\n\nAnd somewhere, an iPhone was pairing, copying symbols into the dark."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":17882,"output":374,"cacheRead":128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18384,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777446196732,"responseId":"0640e0393ea4bfe5587bc6f48d9ce3e1"}}
